    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section" id="faqs">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">Everything you need to know about JayVian protection</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        What devices do you cover?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        We cover all smartphones valued up to 20,000 KES, regardless of brand or model. This includes Android and iOS devices purchased within the last 2 years.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        How soon can I file a claim after signing up?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        You can file a claim after 90 days of continuous premium payments. This waiting period ensures the sustainability of our protection program. After this period, you're eligible for one claim per year.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        What documents do I need to file a claim?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        You'll need: (1) Police abstract report, (2) Copy of your ID, (3) Proof of device ownership (receipt or box), and (4) Your device IMEI number.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        How does the 3-level referral program work?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Our referral program has three levels:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Level 1:</strong> Direct referrals - earn 10% of their monthly premium</li>
                            <li><strong>Level 2:</strong> Referrals of your referrals - earn 5% of their monthly premium</li>
                            <li><strong>Level 3:</strong> Referrals of Level 2 referrals - earn 1% of their monthly premium</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>There's a maximum earning cap of 1,000,000 KES through the referral program.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        What are the withdrawal terms for referral earnings?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>When you withdraw your referral earnings, a 20% commission is applied. This commission covers:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Government taxes required by Kenyan law</li>
                            <li>Transaction processing fees</li>
                            <li>Program administration costs</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>For example: If you withdraw 1,000 KES, you'll receive 800 KES after commission.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        How many claims can I make per year?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        You can make one claim per year after the initial 90-day waiting period. The maximum payout per claim is 20,000 KES.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question">
                        What if I want to cancel my protection?
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        You can cancel anytime with no penalties. We offer a 30-day money-back guarantee for new customers. After that, you can cancel and your protection will end at the end of your current billing cycle.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

